exercise OGNL reflective/property access on JDK 17+ with Test JVM args `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`. Do not set `ognl.security.manager` globally; if testing OGNL security-manager behavior, set and restore that system property inside the specific test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The observed javaTest failure for 3.3.5 appears to be a behavioral/test-expectation mismatch in existing ObjectPropertyAccessor coverage, not a missing dependency or external service.\",\n    \"SecurityManager-related coverage is fragile on JDK 25 because those APIs are deprecated/being removed.\",\n    \"Expression compiler coverage uses Javassist dynamic bytecode generation; JVM tests may pass while Native Image still requires separate metadata verification.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0499cbcf566b6aba016a417bec7fd08197ac65a9fda034e3f4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3153, "output": 1017, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41034, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782676449471, "responseId": "resp_0499cbcf566b6aba016a417be1ed888197b14c6466aa4f7584"}}
